FBIS4-32292 "dreeu121_h_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 HUNGARY `Temporary' Management of National TV, Radio `Temporary' Management of National TV, Radio LD2206145294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1400 GMT 22 Jun 94 LD2206145294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Hungarian BFN [Excerpt] The outgoing prime minister and the HSP [Hungarian Socialist Party] and SZDSZ [Alliance of Free Democrats] leaders have agreed that the current economic directors of Hungarian Television and Hungarian Radio should be entrusted with the management of the two bodies on a temporary basis. The HSP and the SZDSZ are preparing to form a government coalition. The three politicians' explain their decision by the need to avoid a leaderless state of affairs in the two national media institutions. This is contained, among other things, in the government communique published after the morning meeting of Peter Boross [outgoing prime minister], Gyula Horn [HSP candidate for the post of prime minister] and SZDSZ Chairman Ivan Petoe. [passage omitted]
